cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CR 

This paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves mapping between different data models, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The use of Bayesian Networks and First-Order Logic suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The development of a software tool for mapping between the two models suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use cases involving critical infrastructure and manufacturing systems suggest a potential connection to computer security (cs.CR).
